A man was left injured following a collision involving two trucks on the N12 outside Fochville, direction Johannesburg on Tuesday.On arrival paramedics found one truck on the side of the road and another laying on its side.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said the patient was found laying on the road and was discovered the he had sustained moderate injuries. A patient was found laying on the road and after being assessed it was found that he sustained moderate injuries. The patient was then transported to hospital for further medical care, Meiring said.-TNA Reporter 